00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:01,180 --> 00:00:06,530
Sayaka, we were best friends.

2
00:00:06,530 --> 00:00:11,160
<i>The one who drugged Sayaka
was her friend from middle school.</i>

3
00:00:14,860 --> 00:00:16,470
Sayaka!

4
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:25,290
<i>I became the detective for Sayaka's sake.</i>

5
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:27,590
<i>For my beloved wife.</i>

6
00:00:30,050 --> 00:00:34,850
<i>It gave me a real sense of purpose.</i>

7
00:00:34,850 --> 00:00:37,660
Sayaka would never know pain in her life.

8
00:00:37,660 --> 00:00:39,270
That's none of your concern!

9
00:00:39,270 --> 00:00:42,990
<i>And when I finally caught the culprit...</i>

10
00:00:44,970 --> 00:00:50,210
<i>I could feel the dopamine overflowing.</i>

11
00:00:51,930 --> 00:00:55,610
<i>To give me such pleasure...</i>

12
00:00:55,610 --> 00:00:58,270
<i>I'm truly blessed</i>

13
00:00:58,270 --> 00:01:01,500
<i>to marry a woman like Sayaka.</i>

14
00:01:02,820 --> 00:01:04,640
<i>Don't worry, Sayaka.</i>

15
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:07,200
<i>Everything has been resolved.</i>

16
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:18,690
How can you eat,
given the circumstances?

17
00:01:18,690 --> 00:01:21,010
I need to make up
for the wedding money I gave.

18
00:01:21,010 --> 00:01:24,080
What are we going to do about her?

19
00:01:25,140 --> 00:01:26,190
Report her?

20
00:01:26,190 --> 00:01:27,470
Let's not get hasty.

21
00:01:27,470 --> 00:01:29,310
She drugged Sayaka!

22
00:01:29,310 --> 00:01:30,910
She gave her sleeping pills.

23
00:01:30,910 --> 00:01:32,020
That's nothing lethal.

24
00:01:32,020 --> 00:01:35,680
Then what about the threat you sent?

25
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:38,410
Threat?

26
00:01:38,410 --> 00:01:42,730
Don't play dumb. I'm asking about the letter.

27
00:01:42,730 --> 00:01:44,550
What letter?

28
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:50,250
I love you, Sayaka.

29
00:01:58,680 --> 00:02:04,350
Kazu. What do you think "true love" means?

30
00:02:09,070 --> 00:02:13,500
You really are a dummy, Sayaka.

31
00:02:22,020 --> 00:02:28,680
The two of us staying together.
That's "true love".

32
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,820
Sayaka?

33
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:54,070
<i>What the... What's going on?</i>

34
00:02:55,180 --> 00:02:58,790
<i>Sayaka? What's happened to you?</i>

35
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:06,280
Are you two getting married?

36
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:10,330
So am I! Look!

37
00:03:10,330 --> 00:03:13,200
There's my husband!

38
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:19,170
<i>How do I deal with this?</i>

39
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:22,590
<i>How can I make myself look "normal"?</i>

40
00:03:22,590 --> 00:03:27,400
He's always by my side,
and loves me, no matter what.

41
00:03:28,140 --> 00:03:29,800
<i>That's it.</i>

42
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,430
He told me,

43
00:03:31,430 --> 00:03:33,080
<i>She's had her wedding ruined.</i>

44
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,260
staying together...

45
00:03:34,260 --> 00:03:36,150
<i>Not once, but twice.</i>

46
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:37,370
is "true love"!

47
00:03:37,370 --> 00:03:40,290
<i>It's causing Sayaka to break down.</i>

48
00:03:40,290 --> 00:03:46,550
I love you, too.
Let's stay together forever, and ever!

49
00:03:47,270 --> 00:03:50,610
<i>Is this something she'll recover from?</i>

50
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:56,120
<i>If she doesn't,
does she become my responsibility?</i>

51
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:59,210
<i>This crazy woman will stay with me, for life?</i>

52
00:04:00,150 --> 00:04:01,650
Stay back!

53
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,040
- What's up with that?
- He pushed her.

54
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:10,500
- What's she going to do?
- She said they were getting married?

55
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,610
Yikes.

56
00:04:15,550 --> 00:04:17,210
Don't go.

57
00:04:19,890 --> 00:04:24,570
Kazu, please. Don't toss me aside.

58
00:04:27,380 --> 00:04:29,860
You won't, right?

59
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:34,170
You vowed to love me for life.

60
00:04:34,170 --> 00:04:37,550
<i>No. I can't. I can't deal with this.</i>

61
00:04:39,830 --> 00:04:44,150
You just said you loved me.

62
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:48,300
<i>This woman is done for.</i>

63
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:51,950
<i>I can't look after her for life.</i>

64
00:04:51,950 --> 00:04:54,770
<i>I've got no obligation to.</i>

65
00:04:54,770 --> 00:04:57,710
<i>Right. A divorce.</i>

66
00:05:01,270 --> 00:05:03,380
Sayaka.

67
00:05:03,380 --> 00:05:08,150
Staying with me won't help you.

68
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:15,030
I only wanted you to become happy, but...

69
00:05:16,150 --> 00:05:20,000
It seems I can't give you that happiness.

70
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,240
I'm sorry.

71
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:46,430
That was embarrassing.

72
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:49,420
What?

73
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:51,680
I knew it.

74
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:55,840
You don't love me at all.

75
00:05:58,470 --> 00:06:00,500
I've had enough.

76
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,400
Let's get divorced.

77
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:08,720
Stunned?

78
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:12,160
That was all just an act, Kazu.

79
00:06:13,990 --> 00:06:16,700
There's something you've misunderstood.

80
00:06:16,700 --> 00:06:19,480
You must think Honoka sent the threat.

81
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:20,530
But she didn't.

82
00:06:20,530 --> 00:06:24,330
I put that letter in the post myself.

83
00:06:24,950 --> 00:06:26,700
You did?

84
00:06:33,630 --> 00:06:36,350
This was all planned out?

85
00:06:36,350 --> 00:06:39,340
The threat, and the sleeping pills, too?

86
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:41,460
No.

87
00:06:41,460 --> 00:06:45,780
The sleeping pills weren't a part of my plan.

88
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:51,090
I didn't even notice Ueno
was "Honoka Aizawa".

89
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:55,830
I can't believe she still holds a grudge
for what happened in middle school.

90
00:06:55,830 --> 00:06:58,230
What a shocker.

91
00:06:58,230 --> 00:07:01,930
Though I admit, she helped me with my tests.

92
00:07:01,930 --> 00:07:04,290
So I guess I'm grateful to her.

93
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:07,490
What tests?

94
00:07:08,450 --> 00:07:10,040
Test one.

95
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:13,100
How would you react, upon reading the threat?

96
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,410
Test two.

97
00:07:14,410 --> 00:07:17,600
Would you accept me, past and all?

98
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,480
Test three.

99
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:23,140
Would you support me,
even if I attempted suicide?

100
00:07:23,140 --> 00:07:24,220
No, don't tell me...

101
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:27,850
Of course I wasn't going to kill myself.

102
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,740
What the hell?

103
00:07:30,740 --> 00:07:33,930
You were amazing, Kazu.

104
00:07:33,930 --> 00:07:36,650
You had perfect scores across the board!

105
00:07:36,650 --> 00:07:39,160
Until now.

106
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:43,420
Test four.

107
00:07:43,420 --> 00:07:48,240
Would you still love me, if I lost my mind?

108
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:55,040
Unfortunately, you failed my final test.

109
00:07:56,330 --> 00:07:58,260
What a shame.

110
00:07:59,850 --> 00:08:02,350
In any case, we're over.

111
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:04,470
I'll send you the divorce papers,

112
00:08:04,470 --> 00:08:07,600
and submit them to your office tomorrow.

113
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,530
No, you can't.

114
00:08:11,530 --> 00:08:13,800
Please, give me another chance.

115
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:17,350
A divorce after the wedding?
Think of the rumors...

116
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:22,500
I love you.

117
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:25,320
You just pretended like you didn't know me.

118
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:29,840
You pushed me aside,
and said you couldn't make me happy.

119
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:34,060
Your declaration of "true love" was a sham.

120
00:08:34,060 --> 00:08:36,980
Don't let some tests decide
there was no love between us.

121
00:08:36,980 --> 00:08:41,010
I had already decided to accept your past.

122
00:08:41,010 --> 00:08:44,530
If that's not love, then what is?

123
00:08:44,530 --> 00:08:48,500
You're being patronizing.

124
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,430
"Accept your past"?

125
00:08:50,430 --> 00:08:52,900
You think you're so magnanimous.

126
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:58,650
I've always disliked how you belittled me.

127
00:08:58,650 --> 00:09:05,270
You only wanted a girl,
who was weaker and submissive to you.

128
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:06,670
No, that's not true.

129
00:09:06,670 --> 00:09:09,410
You don't love me.

130
00:09:09,410 --> 00:09:13,000
You love how you feel
when you're supporting a weak girl.

131
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,400
No, I...

132
00:09:17,590 --> 00:09:19,620
I love you, Sayaka.

133
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:21,320
Really, again?

134
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:25,090
You're acting like a foolish parrot.

135
00:09:25,090 --> 00:09:27,660
What exactly do you love about me?

136
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:30,540
I...

137
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:33,340
I love that you're a great cook.

138
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:36,160
Okay, and?

139
00:09:38,150 --> 00:09:40,250
I love that you're docile.

140
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:43,080
So you love how I'm subservient.

141
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,770
And?

142
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:52,540
I love how our bodies are compatible.

143
00:09:54,500 --> 00:10:01,410
Then why not hire a housemaid,
and buy a doll to pleasure yourself?

144
00:10:03,780 --> 00:10:05,740
Good bye.

145
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:15,750
Don't you dare run, Sayaka.

146
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:21,140
Who'd love an easy woman like you?
Me, that's who.

147
00:10:21,140 --> 00:10:22,460
Hear me?

148
00:10:22,460 --> 00:10:24,350
You'd end up the same with any man.

149
00:10:24,350 --> 00:10:29,420
Make yourself that marketable
"depressed girl", why don't you?

150
00:10:32,620 --> 00:10:34,230
No.

151
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:36,370
No, no... I didn't mean it.

152
00:10:36,370 --> 00:10:38,440
I'm sorry, Sayaka. Let's talk this out, okay?

153
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:40,650
We're husband and wife now.

154
00:10:44,930 --> 00:10:46,960
Sayaka?

155
00:10:58,490 --> 00:11:02,660
Thank you for the warning.

156
00:11:06,390 --> 00:11:07,990
Sayaka.

157
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:13,270
A bit of advice, for your sake.

158
00:11:14,420 --> 00:11:17,200
Don't ever recover, okay?

159
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:21,510
Because if you do, he'll toss you aside.

160
00:11:22,530 --> 00:11:24,150
Like he did with me.

161
00:11:25,380 --> 00:11:26,940
Why would you say that?

162
00:11:26,940 --> 00:11:31,000
I'm not so benevolent
that I'd wish for your happiness.

163
00:11:31,670 --> 00:11:35,340
When she collapsed, I got chills.

164
00:11:35,340 --> 00:11:37,500
I couldn't help but record the whole thing.

165
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:39,250
You're the worst.

166
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:42,470
No.

167
00:11:44,090 --> 00:11:45,790
You are.

168
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:52,810
I was first suspicious when you invited her
to our wedding at all.

169
00:11:53,890 --> 00:11:55,260
But...

170
00:11:57,110 --> 00:11:59,840
- Akira's just a friend.
- No, she's not.

171
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:04,060
Akira...

172
00:12:05,380 --> 00:12:07,940
is your previous wife, isn't she?

173
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:16,250
Was it so wrong to invite her?

174
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:20,650
Who would want to see
their husband's ex-wife at their wedding?

175
00:12:21,370 --> 00:12:25,970
Think of me, who had to see her ex-husband
doting on his new wife.

176
00:12:25,970 --> 00:12:29,020
Why do you think our guest list was so short?

177
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:30,860
You and your constant remarriages...

178
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:32,100
But now we're just...

179
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:34,180
"Friends"? Of course not.

180
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:38,430
Wait, you still...

181
00:12:38,430 --> 00:12:41,450
What? Don't be stupid.

182
00:12:41,450 --> 00:12:46,080
You play the "good guy",
but think nothing of how others feel.

183
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:48,060
The hell?

184
00:12:48,060 --> 00:12:50,740
I bet Sayaka gets depressed too,

185
00:12:50,740 --> 00:12:53,000
just like I used to.

186
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:57,860
<i>You sure love your mentally ill girls, huh?</i>

187
00:12:57,860 --> 00:13:02,580
As we spent time together,
I slowly recovered.

188
00:13:02,580 --> 00:13:06,690
I was appreciative of you, and our marriage.

189
00:13:06,690 --> 00:13:08,970
But you clearly didn't agree.

190
00:13:10,210 --> 00:13:12,790
You couldn't be happy for her.

191
00:13:12,790 --> 00:13:13,990
I said I'd support...

192
00:13:13,990 --> 00:13:16,840
You wanted to support me so badly?

193
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:21,410
Pathetic.

194
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:26,500
I thought it was for the best.

195
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:28,610
I searched for the culprit, for your sake.

196
00:13:28,610 --> 00:13:31,000
You were just enjoying yourself.

197
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:35,500
It was the spice to your mundane life.

198
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:36,450
I just...

199
00:13:36,450 --> 00:13:40,410
Did it for the sake of your "beloved wife"?

200
00:13:40,410 --> 00:13:42,550
Then of course you'd work hard.

201
00:13:42,550 --> 00:13:46,030
I just wanted to protect you.

202
00:13:53,410 --> 00:13:55,620
Get a life.

203
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:05,510
Protect you, support you, blah, blah, blah.

204
00:14:05,510 --> 00:14:09,730
You certainly love to wax poetic.

205
00:14:09,730 --> 00:14:13,010
Your support is barely surface level.

206
00:14:13,010 --> 00:14:18,200
I was happy to hear you work for "my sake".

207
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:22,870
But it was really
for your own self-satisfaction.

208
00:14:27,190 --> 00:14:31,420
Kazuomi. Do you want Sayaka to become happy?

209
00:14:31,420 --> 00:14:36,230
- Huh?
- Do you honestly want her to find happiness?

210
00:14:36,230 --> 00:14:38,190
Of course, I...

211
00:14:43,890 --> 00:14:45,830
Thought so.

212
00:14:45,830 --> 00:14:47,770
I could tell, you know?

213
00:14:47,770 --> 00:14:52,600
You wanted me to stay
a depressed, obedient girl.

214
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:58,480
Otherwise you can't be the hero.

215
00:14:58,480 --> 00:14:59,540
No.

216
00:14:59,540 --> 00:15:03,950
All that "good intent"
you love preaching about?

217
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:07,670
It was never for anyone else's sake.

218
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:10,160
Everything you do comes right back at you,

219
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,420
and serves to boosts your own ego.

220
00:15:14,910 --> 00:15:18,290
So quit saying it's for "my sake".

221
00:15:24,310 --> 00:15:26,660
You seriously give me the creeps.

222
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:32,570
Then...

223
00:15:32,570 --> 00:15:35,440
Then what should I have done?

224
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,590
I sacrificed so much for you.

225
00:15:37,590 --> 00:15:41,730
Hey. Quit playing the victim.

226
00:15:45,170 --> 00:15:47,650
You think you've been so charitable.

227
00:15:50,300 --> 00:15:55,540
But that "kindness",
is only a burden to others.

228
00:16:14,650 --> 00:16:17,730
[Sayaka Wakamatsu]

229
00:16:37,380 --> 00:16:44,080
<i>A broken-hearted man turns over a new leaf,
and preaches "love", like Romeo.</i>

230
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:51,160
<i>But Kazuomi Hayashida is no Romeo.
He is a self-conceited clown.</i>

231
00:16:52,890 --> 00:16:56,310
You know your mother needs you, Sapphire.

232
00:16:56,310 --> 00:16:59,740
<i>When he declared this woman was a stalker,</i>

233
00:16:59,740 --> 00:17:02,270
<i>I couldn't help but laugh.</i>

234
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:04,580
<i>If he knew this was my mother,</i>

235
00:17:04,580 --> 00:17:06,260
<i>I bet that man</i>

236
00:17:06,260 --> 00:17:09,340
<i>would use his self-serving "good intentions"
as an excuse for the mistake.</i>

237
00:17:09,340 --> 00:17:11,840
You haven't returned
any of the money I lent you.

238
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:15,430
Sapphire, please.

239
00:17:16,990 --> 00:17:19,710
This is the last time.

240
00:17:19,710 --> 00:17:21,780
Now that's my son.

241
00:17:21,780 --> 00:17:23,920
I love you!

242
00:17:25,410 --> 00:17:27,410
Love you lots!

243
00:17:32,340 --> 00:17:36,000
Did your mother leave?

244
00:17:41,730 --> 00:17:43,730
Good morning, Sayaka.

245
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,350
Morning.

246
00:18:00,020 --> 00:18:04,280
You're in high spirits, Sakuraba.

247
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:08,690
Maybe it's because you stayed the night.

248
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:16,280
<i>I needed the perfect subject
for my exhibition to be recognized.</i>

249
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:22,530
<i>And when I saw her, wedding dress and all,
I knew she was the one.</i>

250
00:18:22,530 --> 00:18:24,630
Can I get some shots today?

251
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:31,460
<i>From behind my camera,</i>

252
00:18:31,460 --> 00:18:34,050
<i>the Hayashida couple
felt like a sham wrapped in a bow.</i>

253
00:18:34,050 --> 00:18:35,800
<i>So I made a proposition.</i>

254
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:44,230
Why not test to see
if your husband truly loves you?

255
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:50,030
Can you edit this picture for me?

256
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:57,680
I want to see if he will still love me,

257
00:18:58,790 --> 00:19:03,860
even if I'm not the woman he thought I was.

258
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:12,020
<i>A rash individual like Kazuomi
never had this thought cross his mind.</i>

259
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:16,120
<i>That the "nice guy" who assisted him,</i>

260
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:20,220
<i>had a very hand in the threat.</i>

261
00:19:20,910 --> 00:19:26,770
<i>Let alone plotted the downfall</i>

262
00:19:26,770 --> 00:19:30,300
<i>of their married life itself.</i>

263
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:37,090
<i>Yes, she's the perfect subject.</i>

264
00:19:37,090 --> 00:19:40,370
<i>And now she's all mine.</i>

265
00:19:40,370 --> 00:19:44,000
I wish I'd met you earlier, Sakuraba.

266
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:50,420
Then I could've avoided
that narcissist entirely.

267
00:19:51,090 --> 00:19:58,140
<i>She instinctively seeks a host
who will save her.</i>

268
00:19:58,140 --> 00:20:02,490
<i>This woman,
who so quickly abandoned that man,</i>

269
00:20:02,490 --> 00:20:05,570
<i>now attempts to feed off of me.</i>

270
00:20:05,570 --> 00:20:07,820
Received any new love letters recently?

271
00:20:07,820 --> 00:20:12,580
He hasn't sent any more after the 10th one.

272
00:20:15,620 --> 00:20:18,260
"I was wrong."

273
00:20:18,260 --> 00:20:23,070
"I'm happy to see you moving on, Sayaka."

274
00:20:23,070 --> 00:20:26,630
"If possible, I want to be at your side."

275
00:20:27,590 --> 00:20:31,720
I couldn't read any more than that.

276
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:33,820
I'm here for you now.

277
00:20:35,630 --> 00:20:39,440
I can't believe I met someone like you.

278
00:20:40,790 --> 00:20:45,330
I'm truly blessed.

279
00:20:45,330 --> 00:20:47,240
<i>Are you, now?</i>

280
00:20:49,390 --> 00:20:54,670
<i>I only fell for her face.</i>

281
00:20:54,670 --> 00:20:56,780
<i>I have no earnest love for her.</i>

282
00:20:56,780 --> 00:20:57,920
[Loveri]

283
00:20:57,920 --> 00:21:01,260
"You've been matched with Yuki".

284
00:21:03,020 --> 00:21:05,180
What's this about?

285
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:10,000
You're so busy with work all the time.

286
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:14,960
- I got lonely.
- I don't tolerate any cheating.

287
00:21:14,960 --> 00:21:19,240
<i>I wouldn't want any diseases
transmitting to her.</i>

288
00:21:20,620 --> 00:21:22,160
I'm sorry.

289
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,870
I won't.

290
00:21:23,870 --> 00:21:26,870
I'll delete the app, and my account, too.

291
00:21:26,870 --> 00:21:30,180
<i>She needs to be educated.</i>

292
00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:46,190
Do you promise to only look at me?

293
00:21:50,180 --> 00:21:52,180
I love you.

294
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:56,510
You love me too, right?

295
00:21:58,160 --> 00:22:00,120
Of course.

296
00:22:02,420 --> 00:22:06,180
Let's continue our photoshoot.

297
00:22:07,450 --> 00:22:09,990
- Ready?
- Yeah.

298
00:22:09,990 --> 00:22:13,880
<i>I must make Sayaka</i>

299
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:18,030
<i>the absolute, perfect subject.</i>

300
00:22:18,030 --> 00:22:21,220
<i>So I'll correct her flaws, one by one.</i>

301
00:22:24,190 --> 00:22:26,700
<i>Everything is for her sake.</i>

302
00:22:31,050 --> 00:22:33,040
<i>Not.</i>

303
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:40,610
<i>Are the people around you
truly as good as they say they are?</i>

304
00:22:40,610 --> 00:22:44,470
Do you, the groom,
take her as your lawfully wedded wife?

305
00:22:44,470 --> 00:22:46,990
Yes, I do.

306
00:22:49,530 --> 00:22:53,190
<i>Is the person you're facing now,</i>

307
00:22:54,070 --> 00:22:58,950
<i>truly taking action for your sake?</i>

